524
00:37:02.800 --> 00:37:04.600
Confidant.

525
00:37:04.600 --> 00:37:07.000
What's wrong with the sun this time?

526
00:37:10.600 --> 00:37:14.500
It suddenly appeared in front of us,
humongous.

527
00:37:15.600 --> 00:37:16.800
I don't understand.

528
00:37:16.800 --> 00:37:22.700
In other words, as if in our world, the sun just rose at dawn,

529
00:37:22.700 --> 00:37:27.900
but one second later, precisely one second later, it jumped to the position of noon.

530
00:37:27.900 --> 00:37:34.800
And according to Mozi, in the time of Confucius, the sun went out all of a sudden.

531
00:37:36.200 --> 00:37:38.500
He still doesn't understand.

532
00:37:39.600 --> 00:37:41.000
Look.

533
00:37:43.000 --> 00:37:46.800
Hypothetically, this was the sun
in the time of Confucius.

534
00:37:48.000 --> 00:37:50.800
It went out all of a sudden.

535
00:37:52.100 --> 00:37:54.000
Does the sun have a switch?

536
00:37:54.000 --> 00:37:55.400
That's impossible.

537
00:37:55.400 --> 00:37:57.600
But the sun can move.

538
00:37:57.600 --> 00:38:01.100
It can move away from
or close to us very fast,

539
00:38:01.100 --> 00:38:06.400
as fast as if it is switched on or off.

540
00:38:06.400 --> 00:38:08.100
Understood.

541
00:38:09.500 --> 00:38:14.000
In the time of Confucius,
the sun moved away very fast.

542
00:38:14.000 --> 00:38:17.000
In the time of Mozi,
the sun came close very fast.

543
00:38:17.000 --> 00:38:18.400
Exactly.

544
00:38:19.900 --> 00:38:23.000
And Mozi disclosed
very important information.

545
00:38:23.000 --> 00:38:29.500
In the time of Confucius, after the sun went out suddenly, a flying star appeared in the sky.

546
00:38:29.500 --> 00:38:33.000
If it was true,
I think there is only one possibility.

547
00:38:33.000 --> 00:38:40.000
After the sun went out, the flying star that was originally covered by the sun's rays became visible.

548
00:38:42.800 --> 00:38:45.100
I don't understand.

549
00:38:47.800 --> 00:38:49.000
- Do you have a flashlight?
- Yes.

550
00:38:49.000 --> 00:38:50.800
Find me one.

551
00:38:52.000 --> 00:38:55.300
That's the sun.

552
00:38:55.300 --> 00:38:57.300
This is the flying star.

553
00:39:02.700 --> 00:39:04.200
We can't see it.

554
00:39:04.200 --> 00:39:08.200
The sun's light is so strong
that it overshadows the flying star.

555
00:39:08.200 --> 00:39:10.710
But after the sun goes out,

556
00:39:11.800 --> 00:39:15.300
Look, the flying star appears.

557
00:39:17.200 --> 00:39:19.300
There must be some connection.

558
00:39:19.300 --> 00:39:21.700
But I haven't figured it out yet.

559
00:39:21.700 --> 00:39:25.400
I need further observation
to figure it out.

560
00:39:25.400 --> 00:39:27.000
Can the sun move that fast?

561
00:39:27.000 --> 00:39:28.000
It's impossible.

562
00:39:28.000 --> 00:39:31.200
In the world of Three-Body,
it's possible.

